      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Feeling like you are the problem because your pain projects onto your children is a common hurtful distortion many parents experience during tough times. It is rarely ever \"selfish\" to stay when pain or hurt feelings hurt your children more than it hurts you to be hurt. Your presence, even when difficult, often means they know you are in pain and not just ignoring them, which can actually build resilience in them. Please reach out to a professional today who can help you untangle these feelings and guide you on how to support your children without becoming overwhelmed by your own pain.",
